CPC Corp., a Taiwan state-run oil
company, bought 5 million barrels of Angolan crude for loading
in August via a tender, according to five traders who
participate in the market.  The company bought 3 million barrels of Cabinda and 2
million barrels of the Nemba grade, according to the people, who
declined to be identified because the information is
confidential. CPC awarded the tender to  Chevron Corp. (CVX) ,  Total SA (FP) 
and  Eni SpA. (ENI)   CPC also bought 1 million barrels of Caspian Azeri Light
crude from Socar Trading SA, they said.  Details of the purchases are as follows:  To contact the reporter on this story:
